# 🏛️ Court Transparency System — Implementation Plan

## Decisions Locked ✅

| Decision | Choice |
|:---|:---|
| **Database** | PostgreSQL via Docker |
| **Redis** | Redis via Docker |
| **OTP** | Simulated (console log + Redis) |
| **Build Order** | Backend-first, then frontend |
| **AI** | Google Gemini (pluggable, works without key too) |
| **Deployment** | Docker Compose locally → Cloud later |

---

## 🔨 Build Stages (Backend-First)

### Stage 1: Project Scaffold & Docker Setup
- [ ] Initialize Node.js project with Express
- [ ] Create `docker-compose.yml` (PostgreSQL + Redis + Node app)
- [ ] Create `Dockerfile` for backend
- [ ] Setup environment config (`.env` + validation)
- [ ] Setup PostgreSQL connection with `pg` driver
- [ ] Setup Redis connection with `ioredis`
- [ ] Create Express app skeleton with health check endpoint
- [ ] Test: `docker-compose up` → API responds on `/health`

