### Stage 9: AI Integration (Pluggable)
- [ ] AI service wrapper (Google Gemini)
- [ ] Graceful fallback if no API key (skip AI, log warning)
- [ ] Document text extraction (OCR via Gemini Vision)
- [ ] Document summarization
- [ ] Delay reason classification
- [ ] BullMQ queue for async AI processing
- [ ] AI worker that processes queue jobs
- [ ] Test: Upload doc → AI job enqueued → summary stored (or skipped if no key)

---

### Stage 10: Delay Detection Engine
- [ ] Delay detection worker (BullMQ repeatable job, every 6 hours)
- [ ] Scan all active cases for:
  - No update > 30 days → warning (score 3-5)
  - No update > 60 days → high risk (score 6-8)
  - No update > 90 days → critical (score 9-10)
- [ ] Update `delay_risk_score` in PostgreSQL
- [ ] Add case IDs to Redis delay sets (`delay:warning`, `delay:high_risk`, `delay:critical`)
- [ ] Generate alerts for affected cases
- [ ] Stagnation flag detection
- [ ] Test: Create case with old date → run worker → verify alert created + Redis set updated

---

### Stage 11: Reminder & Alert System
- [ ] Hearing reminder worker (BullMQ repeatable, every hour)
  - Next hearing in 3 days → alert
  - Next hearing in 1 day → alert
- [ ] Alert CRUD endpoints (get alerts, mark read, mark all read)
- [ ] Alert generation service (creates alerts in DB)
- [ ] Test: Set hearing date 1 day ahead → run worker → verify reminder alert

---

### Stage 12: Leaderboard & Analytics Engine
- [ ] Leaderboard computation service:
  - Cases resolved count
  - Average resolution time
  - Adjournment rate
  - Backlog size
  - Justice Speed Index (composite score)
- [ ] Store rankings in Redis sorted sets
- [ ] Leaderboard refresh worker (BullMQ repeatable, every 6 hours)
- [ ] Leaderboard API endpoint (public)
- [ ] Admin analytics endpoints (court-wise breakdown)
- [ ] Test: Seed multiple cases + courts → run leaderboard refresh → verify rankings

