### Stage 14: Victim-Controlled Disclosure System
- [ ] Submit disclosure request (select fields: accused_name, judge_name, timeline)
- [ ] AI safety check (does disclosure risk identifying victim?)
- [ ] Admin review endpoint (approve/reject with notes)
- [ ] On approval: update case.disclosure_mode + case.disclosed_fields
- [ ] Revoke disclosure (victim can take back)
- [ ] Public case view respects disclosure_mode
- [ ] Audit log for all disclosure actions
- [ ] Test: Submit request → admin approve → verify public view shows disclosed fields → revoke → verify removed

